{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775877397593,"sessionID":"ses_285759645ffe2slctD9Dn1azJE","part":{"id":"prt_d7a8a9a84001OGVvY7zbo0ZsXJ","messageID":"msg_d7a8a8e26001O8h68aTSJOvrlb","sessionID":"ses_285759645ffe2slctD9Dn1azJE","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_ba742d1f653e4620a11b1692","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-032 — Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images)\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Provide three multi-stage Dockerfiles to build production-ready container images for AgentCube's core binaries: Workload Manager, Router, and picod. Each Dockerfile separates the Go compilation stage from the minimal runtime stage, reducing final image size, eliminating build-time dependencies from production images, and running binaries as non-root users where security permits. The images are built via Makefile targets and loaded into Kind for E2E testing or pushed to `ghcr.io/volcano-sh` for production deployment.\n6: \n7: ## Scope\n8: \n9: ### In scope\n10: \n11: | Item | Detail |\n12: |------|--------|\n13: | **`docker/Dockerfile`** | Workload Manager multi-stage build (golang:1.24.9-alpine → alpine:3.19) |\n14: | **`docker/Dockerfile.router`** | Router multi-stage build (golang:1.24.9-alpine → alpine:3.19) |\n15: | **`docker/Dockerfile.picod`** | picod multi-stage build (golang:1.24.4 → ubuntu:24.04) |\n16: | **Makefile targets** | `docker-build`, `docker-build-router`, `docker-build-picod` and their buildx/push/kind-load variants |\n17: | **Build context** | Repository root (all three Dockerfiles use `.` as context) |\n18: | **Multi-arch support** | `docker-buildx` targets for linux/amd64 and linux/arm64 |\n19: | **Non-root runtime** | `apiserver` (UID 1000) for workloadmanager, `router` (UID 1000) for router |\n20: | **Security hardening** | `CGO_ENABLED=0`, `-ldflags=\"-s -w\"`, minimal base images, ca-certificates only |\n21: \n22: ### Out of scope\n23: \n24: - `example/pcap-analyzer/Dockerfile` (separate AR, Python-based example)\n25: - CI/CD pipeline integration for automated image push (covered by ci-cd spec)\n26: - Helm chart image tag management (handled by `values.yaml`)\n27: - Docker Compose orchestration (not required for AgentCube deployment model)\n28: - Image scanning / SBOM generation\n29: - Runtime user for picod (runs as root by design — requires `chattr` on pubkey and sandbox permissions)\n30: \n31: ## Design\n32: \n33: ### File layout\n34: \n35: | File | Role |\n36: |------|------|\n37: | `docker/Dockerfile` | Workload Manager: 2-stage build, outputs `workloadmanager` binary |\n38: | `docker/Dockerfile.router` | Router: 2-stage build, outputs `agentcube-router` binary |\n39: | `docker/Dockerfile.picod` | picod: 2-stage build, outputs `picod` binary |\n40: \n41: ### `docker/Dockerfile` (Workload Manager)\n42: \n43: ```dockerfile\n44: # Build stage\n45: FROM golang:1.24.9-alpine AS builder\n46: WORKDIR /workspace\n47: COPY go.mod go.sum ./\n48: RUN go mod download\n49: COPY cmd/ cmd/\n50: COPY pkg/ pkg/\n51: RUN --mount=type=cache,target=/root/.cache/go-build \\\n52:     CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=${TARGETOS} GOARCH=${TARGETARCH} \\\n53:     go build -ldflags=\"-s -w\" -o workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager\n54: \n55: # Runtime stage\n56: FROM alpine:3.19\n57: RUN apk add --no-cache ca-certificates\n58: WORKDIR /app\n59: COPY --from=builder /workspace/workloadmanager /app/workloadmanager\n60: RUN adduser -D -u 1000 apiserver\n61: USER apiserver\n62: EXPOSE 8080\n63: ENTRYPOINT [\"/app/workloadmanager\"]\n64: CMD [\"--port=8080\"]\n65: ```\n66: \n67: | Stage | Detail |\n68: |-------|--------|\n69: | builder | `golang:1.24.9-alpine`; copies only `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `cmd/`, `pkg/`; BuildKit cache mount for `go build`; `CGO_ENABLED=0` for static binary; `-ldflags=\"-s -w\"` strips debug symbols |\n70: | runtime | `alpine:3.19`; only `ca-certificates` installed; binary copied from builder; non-root user `apiserver` UID 1000; exposes 8080 |\n71: \n72: Build args: `TARGETOS=linux` (default), `TARGETARCH` (set by buildx platform).\n73: \n74: ### `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n75: \n76: ```dockerfile\n77: # Build stage\n78: FROM golang:1.24.9-alpine AS builder\n79: WORKDIR /workspace\n80: COPY go.mod go.sum ./\n81: RUN go mod download\n82: COPY cmd/ cmd/\n83: COPY pkg/ pkg/\n84: COPY client-go/ client-go/\n85: RUN --mount=type=cache,target=/root/.cache/go-build \\\n86:     CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=${TARGETOS} GOARCH=${TARGETARCH} \\\n87:     go build -ldflags=\"-s -w\" -o agentcube-router ./cmd/router\n88: \n89: # Runtime stage\n90: FROM alpine:3.19\n91: RUN apk add --no-cache ca-certificates\n92: WORKDIR /app\n93: COPY --from=builder /workspace/agentcube-router /app/agentcube-router\n94: RUN adduser -D -u 1000 router\n95: USER router\n96: EXPOSE 8080\n97: ENTRYPOINT [\"/app/agentcube-router\"]\n98: CMD [\"--port=8080\", \"--debug\"]\n99: ```\n100: \n101: | Stage | Detail |\n102: |-------|--------|\n103: | builder | Same as workloadmanager, plus `COPY client-go/ client-go/` (generated Kubernetes clientset); outputs `agentcube-router` from `./cmd/router` |\n104: | runtime | `alpine:3.19`; non-root user `router` UID 1000; default CMD includes `--debug` flag |\n105: \n106: ### `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n107: \n108: ```dockerfile\n109: # Build stage\n110: FROM golang:1.24.4 AS builder\n111: WORKDIR /app\n112: COPY go.mod go.sum ./\n113: RUN go mod download\n114: COPY . .\n115: RUN CGO_ENABLED=0 go build -o picod ./cmd/picod\n116: \n117: # Runtime stage\n118: FROM ubuntu:24.04\n119: RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y python3\n120: WORKDIR /root/\n121: COPY --from=builder /app/picod ./picod\n122: # Runs as root: chattr on pubkey + sandbox permissions require elevated privileges\n123: ENTRYPOINT [\"./picod\"]\n124: ```\n125: \n126: | Stage | Detail |\n127: |-------|--------|\n128: | builder | `golang:1.24.4` (note: different version from control plane); `COPY . .` copies entire repo (picod is a separate module at repo root); no BuildKit cache mount |\n129: | runtime | `ubuntu:24.04` (not Alpine — requires `python3` for sandbox subprocess execution); runs as root (comment documents rationale) |\n130: \n131: ### Makefile Docker targets\n132: \n133: | Target | Command |\n134: |--------|---------|\n135: | `docker-build` | `$(CONTAINER_TOOL) build -f docker/Dockerfile -t $(WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE) .` |\n136: | `docker-build-router` | `$(CONTAINER_TOOL) build -f docker/Dockerfile.router -t $(ROUTER_IMAGE) .` |\n137: | `docker-build-picod` | `$(CONTAINER_TOOL) build -f docker/Dockerfile.picod -t $(PICOD_IMAGE) .` |\n138: | `docker-buildx` | `docker buildx build --platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64 -f docker/Dockerfile -t $(HUB)/workloadmanager:$(TAG) .` |\n139: | `docker-buildx-router` | Same pattern for router image |\n140: | `docker-buildx-picod` | Same pattern for picod image |\n141: | `docker-buildx-push` | As above with `--push`; requires `IMAGE_REGISTRY` set |\n142: | `docker-buildx-push-router` | Same for router |\n143: | `docker-buildx-push-picod` | Same for picod |\n144: | `docker-push` | `docker tag` + `docker push` for workloadmanager |\n145: | `docker-push-router` | Same for router |\n146: | `docker-push-picod` | Same for picod |\n147: | `kind-load` | `kind load docker-image $(WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE) --name $(E2E_CLUSTER_NAME)` |\n148: | `kind-load-router` | Same for router |\n149: \n150: ### Image characteristics\n151: \n152: | Image | Builder base | Runtime base | Binary | User | Port |\n153: |-------|-------------|--------------|--------|------|------|\n154: | workloadmanager | golang:1.24.9-alpine | alpine:3.19 | `workloadmanager` | apiserver (1000) | 8080 |\n155: | agentcube-router | golang:1.24.9-alpine | alpine:3.19 | `agentcube-router` | router (1000) | 8080 |\n156: | picod | golang:1.24.4 | ubuntu:24.04 | `picod` | root | N/A |\n157: \n158: ## Impact analysis\n159: \n160: ### Files created\n161: \n162: | File | Lines (est.) |\n163: |------|-------------|\n164: | `docker/Dockerfile` | ~18 |\n165: | `docker/Dockerfile.router` | ~20 |\n166: | `docker/Dockerfile.picod` | ~14 |\n167: \n168: ### Files modified\n169: \n170: | File | Change |\n171: |------|--------|\n172: | `Makefile` | Add `docker-build`, `docker-build-router`, `docker-build-picod` targets and variants |\n173: \n174: ### Dependencies\n175: \n176: | Dependency | Usage |\n177: |------------|-------|\n178: | Docker / Podman | Container image build runtime (`CONTAINER_TOOL` variable) |\n179: | BuildKit | Cache mount support in builder stage (`--mount=type=cache`) |\n180: | docker buildx | Multi-arch cross-compilation (`--platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64`) |\n181: | Kind | E2E image loading (`kind load docker-image`) |\n182: \n183: ### Downstream consumers\n184: \n185: | Consumer | Dependency |\n186: |----------|-----------|\n187: | `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` | References image `repository:tag` for each component |\n188: | `test/e2e/run_e2e.sh` | Expects images built and loaded into Kind cluster |\n189: | GitHub Actions CI | Calls `docker-buildx-push` targets for automated publishing |\n190: | Helm install command | Uses image names from `values.yaml` overrides |\n191: \n192: ### Breaking change risk\n193: \n194: **None**: These are new files. No existing Dockerfiles or build processes are replaced.\n195: \n196: ### Performance characteristics\n197: \n198: - **Build cache efficiency**: `go.mod`/`go.sum` copied before source code — dependency download cached independently of code changes\n199: - **BuildKit cache mount**: `/root/.cache/go-build` persisted across builds, reducing compile time for unchanged packages\n200: - **Final image size**: Alpine runtime (~5-10 MB) vs full golang image (~300+ MB); estimated 95%+ size reduction\n201: - **Multi-arch**: Single `docker-buildx` invocation produces both amd64 and arm64 manifests\n202: \n203: ### Edge cases handled\n204: \n205: 1. **Cross-platform build**: `GOOS=${TARGETOS} GOARCH=${TARGETARCH}` build args set by buildx for correct target architecture\n206: 2. **Static binary**: `CGO_ENABLED=0` ensures no dynamic library dependencies on Alpine runtime\n207: 3. **Symbol stripping**: `-ldflags=\"-s -w\"` removes debug info and symbol table, further reducing binary size\n208: 4. **picod root requirement**: Documented in Dockerfile comment; cannot run as non-root due to `chattr` and sandbox permission requirements\n209: 5. **Go version divergence**: picod uses golang:1.24.4 (not 1.24.9) — pinned to picod module's tested version\n210: \n211: ## Alternatives considered\n212: \n213: ### 1. Single-stage Dockerfiles\n214: \n215: **Approach**: Use full `golang` image as runtime, compile and run in the same stage.\n216: \n217: **Rejected because**:\n218: - Final image size ~300-500 MB vs ~10 MB for multi-stage (30-50x larger)\n219: - Exposes build toolchain (compiler, linker, source code) in production image — security risk\n220: - Longer pull times for deployment, especially in air-gapped or low-bandwidth environments\n221: - Violates container best practice of minimal runtime images\n222: \n223: ### 2. Distroless base images (gcr.io/distroless/static)\n224: \n225: **Approach**: Use Google's distroless images as runtime base instead of Alpine.\n226: \n227: **Rejected because**:\n228: - Distroless `static` has no package manager — cannot install `ca-certificates` or `python3` (required by picod)\n229: - Distroless `base` (Debian-based) is larger than Alpine (~20 MB vs ~5 MB)\n230: - picod requires `python3` at runtime — distroless does not provide it without custom extension\n231: - Alpine provides sufficient minimalism with `apk` for the few required packages\n232: - Workload Manager and Router only need `ca-certificates` — Alpine handles this with negligible overhead\n233: \n234: ### 3. Shared builder image for all three binaries\n235: \n236: **Approach**: Single Dockerfile with multiple builder stages and multiple runtime stages, producing all three binaries from one build.\n237: \n238: **Rejected because**:\n239: - Violates single-responsibility: one Dockerfile per deployable artifact is standard practice\n240: - Forces rebuild of all binaries when only one changes (no independent caching)\n241: - picod requires different Go version (1.24.4) and full repo copy (`COPY . .`) — incompatible with control-plane builder\n242: - Helm chart expects separate image repositories (`workloadmanager`, `agentcube-router`, `picod`)\n243: - CI/CD pipelines build and push images independently per component\n244: \n245: ### 4. Binary-only COPY from pre-built artifacts\n246: \n247: **Approach**: CI builds Go binaries on host/runner, Dockerfile only copies pre-compiled binary into runtime image.\n248: \n249: **Rejected because**:\n250: - Loses reproducibility: Docker build no longer self-contained — depends on external build environment\n251: - Cross-compilation complexity shifts from Docker build args to CI matrix configuration\n252: - No build cache benefit — every CI run recompiles from scratch\n253: - Developer local builds (`make docker-build`) would require matching Go toolchain on host\n254: - Multi-stage Dockerfile provides identical output with better encapsulation\n255: \n256: ### 5. Ubuntu runtime for all images (uniformity)\n257: \n258: **Approach**: Use `ubuntu:24.04` as runtime base for all three images instead of mixing Alpine and Ubuntu.\n259: \n260: **Rejected because**:\n261: - Workload Manager and Router are pure Go static binaries — Ubuntu's glibc, coreutils, and package manager add ~70 MB of unnecessary attack surface\n262: - picod requires Ubuntu for `python3` — this is a genuine dependency, not a preference\n263: - Alpine's musl libc is compatible with `CGO_ENABLED=0` static binaries (no libc needed at runtime)\n264: - Security scanning would flag Ubuntu images for more CVEs due to larger package footprint\n265: - The marginal benefit of base image uniformity does not outweigh the security and size costs\n\n(End of file - total 265 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-032 — Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images)\n\n## Purpose\n\nProvide three multi-stage Dockerfiles to build production-ready container images for AgentCube's core binaries: Workload Manager, Router, and picod. Each Dockerfile separates the Go compilation stage from the minimal runtime stage, reducing final image size, eliminating build-time dependencies from production images, and running binaries as non-root users where security permits. The images are built via Makefile targets and loaded into Kind for E2E testing or pushed to `ghcr.io/volcano-sh` for production deployment.\n\n## Scope\n\n### In scope\n\n| Item | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **`docker/Dockerfile`** | Workload Manager multi-stage build (golang:1.24.9-alpine → alpine:3.19) |\n| **`docker/Dockerfile.router`** | Router multi-stage build (golang:1.24.9-alpine → alpine:3.19) |\n| **`docker/Dockerfile.picod`** | picod multi-stage build (golang:1.24.4 → ubuntu:24.04) |\n| **Makefile targets** | `docker-build`, `docker-build-router`, `docker-build-picod` and their buildx/push/kind-load variants |\n| **Build context** | Repository root (all three Dockerfiles use `.` as context) |\n| **Multi-arch support** | `docker-buildx` targets for linux/amd64 and linux/arm64 |\n| **Non-root runtime** | `apiserver` (UID 1000) for workloadmanager, `router` (UID 1000) for router |\n| **Security hardening** | `CGO_ENABLED=0`, `-ldflags=\"-s -w\"`, minimal base images, ca-certificates only |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"proposal.md","time":{"start":1775877397584,"end":1775877397590}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775877397618,"sessionID":"ses_285759645ffe2slctD9Dn1azJE","part":{"id":"prt_d7a8a9c58001Uhleux3gFfV3jW","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7a8a8e26001O8h68aTSJOvrlb","sessionID":"ses_285759645ffe2slctD9Dn1azJE","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":18371,"input":3479,"output":52,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":14840}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775877399841,"sessionID":"ses_285759645ffe2slctD9Dn1azJE","part":{"id":"prt_d7a8aa51f001WkPXQVIPsMMuYs","messageID":"msg_d7a8a9c8a001VCBGptRED3IIoH","sessionID":"ses_285759645ffe2slctD9Dn1azJE","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775877464322,"sessionID":"ses_285759645ffe2slctD9Dn1azJE","part":{"id":"prt_d7a8ab0b600130J4Xmnz3rMfmF","messageID":"msg_d7a8a9c8a001VCBGptRED3IIoH","sessionID":"ses_285759645ffe2slctD9Dn1azJE","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_4524e9fa87c946878a124800","state":{"status":"error","input":{"content":"# AR-035 — client-go 类型客户端生成\n\n## Purpose\n\nGenerate Kubernetes client code (client-go) for AgentCube's API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`, enabling in-cluster clients to interact with AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter custom resources. This generated client follows the standard Kubernetes client-go patterns, providing typed clients, listers, informers, and fake clients for testing. The client library will be consumed by the Router component to manage agent runtimes and code interpreters programmatically.\n\n## Scope\n\n### In scope\n\n| Item | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **Module path** | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` |\n| **Source reference** | `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/` |\n| **API group** | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` / `v1alpha1` |\n| **Resource types** | `AgentRuntime`, `CodeInterpreter` |\n| **Clientset** | `Interface` with `RuntimeV1alpha1()` accessor; `Discovery()` and typed client accessors |\n| **Typed clients** | Full CRUD + Watch + Patch for both AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter |\n| **Informers** | `SharedInformerFactory` with namespace-scoped informers |\n| **Listers** | `AgentRuntimeLister`, `CodeInterpreterLister` with namespace support |\n| **Fake clients** | Test doubles for all typed clients and clientset |\n| **Scheme registration** | `AddToScheme` for `runtime/v1alpha1` types |\n| **Makefile targets** | `make gen-client` → `hack/update-codegen.sh` using k8s.io/code-generator v0.34.1 |\n\n### Out of scope\n\n- Custom resource definitions (CRDs) — handled by separate AR\n- Controller implementation using the generated client\n- Client authentication / config handling beyond standard client-go patterns\n- Client-rate limiting or custom retry logic\n- Integration with Volcano scheduler\n- Versioned API (v1beta1 or other versions) — v1alpha1 only for this AR\n\n## Design\n\n### File layout\n\n| Path | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `client-go/clientset/versioned/clientset.go` | `Clientset`, `Interface`, constructors |\n| `client-go/clientset/versioned/scheme/register.go` | Scheme / codecs for generated client |\n| `client-go/clientset/versioned/scheme/doc.go` | Doc |\n| `client-go/clientset/versioned/fake/clientset_generated.go` | Fake clientset implementation |\n| `client-go/clientset/versioned/fake/register.go` | Fake scheme wiring |\n| `client-go/clientset/versioned/fake/doc.go` | Doc |\n| `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/runtime_client.go` | `RuntimeV1alpha1Client`, `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface` |\n| `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | `AgentRuntimeInterface`, typed REST client |\n| `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | `CodeInterpreterInterface`, typed REST client |\n| `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/generated_expansion.go` | Expansion interfaces |\n| `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go` | Doc |\n| `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_runtime_client.go` | Fake runtime group client |\n| `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_agentruntime.go` | Fake AgentRuntime client |\n| `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_codeinterpreter.go` | Fake CodeInterpreter client |\n| `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/doc.go` | Doc |\n| `client-go/informers/externalversions/factory.go` | `SharedInformerFactory`, options, `Start`/`Shutdown`/`WaitForCacheSync` |\n| `client-go/informers/externalversions/generic.go` | `GenericInformer`, `ForResource` |\n| `client-go/informers/externalversions/runtime/interface.go` | Group `runtime` informer accessor |\n| `client-go/informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/interface.go` | `v1alpha1` informer accessors |\n| `client-go/informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | AgentRuntime informer + constructor |\n| `client-go/informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | CodeInterpreter informer + constructor |\n| `client-go/informers/externalversions/internalinterfaces/factory_interfaces.go` | Factory interface + `NewInformerFunc`, `TweakListOptionsFunc` |\n| `client-go/listers/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | `AgentRuntimeLister`, namespace lister |\n| `client-go/listers/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | `CodeInterpreterLister`, namespace lister |\n| `client-go/listers/runtime/v1alpha1/expansion_generated.go` | Lister expansion interfaces |\n\n### Code generation\n\n**Command**: `make gen-client` → `hack/update-codegen.sh`\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# hack/update-codegen.sh\n\nset -e\n\nCODEGEN_VERSION=\"v0.34.1\"\nMODULE_PATH=\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go\"\nSOURCE_DIR=\"/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go\"\n\ngo install k8s.io/code-generator/cmd/client-gen@${CODEGEN_VERSION}\ngo install k8s.io/code-generator/cmd/lister-gen@${CODEGEN_VERSION}\ngo install k8s.io/code-generator/cmd/informer-gen@${CODEGEN_VERSION}\n\nclient-gen \\\n    --input-base=\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube\" \\\n    --input=\"runtime/v1alpha1\" \\\n    --output-package=\"${MODULE_PATH}/clientset\" \\\n    --clientset-name=\"versioned\" \\\n    --with-watch=true \\\n    --apply-configuration-package=\"k8s.io/client-go/applyconfiguration\"\n\nlister-gen \\\n    --input-dirs=\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\" \\\n    --output-package=\"${MODULE_PATH}/listers\"\n\ninformer-gen \\\n    --input-dirs=\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\" \\\n    --versioned-clientset-package=\"${MODULE_PATH}/clientset/versioned\" \\\n    --listers-package=\"${MODULE_PATH}/listers\" \\\n    --output-package=\"${MODULE_PATH}/informers\"\n```\n\n### Clientset interface\n\n```go\ntype Interface interface {\n    Discovery() discovery.DiscoveryInterface\n    RuntimeV1alpha1() runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n}\n\ntype Clientset struct {\n    *discovery.DiscoveryClient\n    runtimeV1alpha1 *runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Client\n}\n\nfunc NewForConfig(c *rest.Config) (*Clientset, error)\nfunc NewForConfigAndClient(c *rest.Config, httpClient *http.Client) (*Clientset, error)\nfunc NewForConfigOrDie(c *rest.Config) *Clientset\nfunc New(c rest.Interface) *Clientset\n```\n\n### Typed client interfaces\n\n**AgentRuntimeInterface**:\n```go\ntype AgentRuntimeInterface interface {\n    RESTClient() rest.Interface\n    Create(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.CreateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    Update(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    UpdateStatus(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    Delete(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.DeleteOptions) error\n    DeleteCollection(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.DeleteOptions, listOpts metav1.ListOptions) error\n    Get(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.GetOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    List(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeList, error)\n    Watch(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (watch.Interface, error)\n    Patch(ctx context.Context, name string, pt types.PatchType, data []byte, opts metav1.PatchOptions, subresources ...string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    AgentRuntimeExpansion\n}\n```\n\nREST resource plural: `agentruntimes`\n\n**CodeInterpreterInterface**: Same method shape for `CodeInterpreter` / `CodeInterpreterList`. REST resource plural: `codeinterpreters`\n\n### Informer factory\n\n```go\ntype SharedInformerFactory interface {\n    Start(stopCh <-chan struct{})\n    Shutdown()\n    WaitForCacheSync(stopCh <-chan struct{}) map[reflect.Type]bool\n    ForResource(resource schema.GroupVersionResource) (GenericInformer, error)\n    InformerFor(obj runtime.Object, newFunc internalinterfaces.NewInformerFunc) cache.SharedIndexInformer\n    Runtime() externalversionsruntime.Interface\n}\n\nfunc NewSharedInformerFactory(client versioned.Interface, defaultResync time.Duration)\nfunc NewSharedInformerFactoryWithOptions(client versioned.Interface, defaultResync time.Duration, options ...SharedInformerOption)\n```\n\n### Lister interfaces\n\n```go\ntype AgentRuntimeLister interface {\n    List(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    AgentRuntimes(namespace string) AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister\n    AgentRuntimeListerExpansion\n}\n\ntype AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister interface {\n    List(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    Get(name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    AgentRuntimeNamespaceListerExpansion\n}\n```\n\nSame pattern for `CodeInterpreterLister` / `CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister`.\n\n## Impact analysis\n\n### Files created\n\n| File | Lines (est.) |\n|------|-------------|\n| `client-go/` directory | ~2500 lines (generated) |\n| `hack/update-codegen.sh` | ~30 lines |\n| `Makefile` additions | ~10 lines |\n\n### Files modified\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `Makefile` | Add `gen-client` target |\n| `go.mod` (client-go) | Add client-go dependencies |\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Usage |\n|------------|-------|\n| `k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1 | Code generation tools |\n| `k8s.io/api` | Kubernetes API definitions |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery` | Kubernetes type utilities |\n| `k8s.io/client-go` | Client generation base |\n| `k8s.io/utils` | Utility functions |\n\n### Downstream consumers\n\n| Consumer | Dependency |\n|----------|-----------|\n| `cmd/router` | Imports `client-go` for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter management |\n| `test/e2e` | Uses fake clients for controller testing |\n| Future controllers | Use listers and informers for caching |\n\n### Breaking change risk\n\n**Low**: This is a new module. Existing code may need to import and use the new client-go module, but no existing functionality is modified.\n\n### Performance characteristics\n\n- **Generation time**: ~10-30 seconds for full client generation\n- **Client runtime**: Standard client-go performance (caching, watch, retry)\n- **Binary size**: Generated code adds ~500KB to client-go module\n- **Informer memory**: Depends on cluster size; uses standard Kubernetes informer caching\n\n### Edge cases handled\n\n1. **Watch support**: Enabled via `--with-watch=true` for real-time resource updates\n2. **Fake clients**: Full test doubles for unit testing without cluster access\n3. **Namespace-scoped operations**: Both namespaced and cluster-scoped listers provided\n4. **Patch operations**: Support for strategic merge patch and JSON patch\n5. **Expansion interfaces**: Empty expansion interfaces reserved for future custom methods\n\n## Alternatives considered\n\n### 1. Manual client implementation\n\n**Approach**: Write typed clients manually without code generation.\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- Violates Kubernetes ecosystem conventions; harder for others to maintain\n- Code generator ensures consistency with upstream client-go patterns\n- Manual maintenance burden for CRUD operations, especially with watch/patch\n- Missing automatic fake client generation requires manual test double maintenance\n\n### 2. Use controller-runtime client\n\n**Approach**: Use `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/client` instead of generating client-go.\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- Router component uses client-go patterns (based on Kubernetes sample controller)\n- Existing codebase already imports client-go; consistency within project\n- controller-runtime client is untyped (uses `Object` interface); typed clients provide better IDE support\n- Informers and listers not provided by controller-runtime by default\n\n### 3. Generate only typed clients, skip informers/listers\n\n**Approach**: Client generation without informer and lister generation.\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- Informers provide significant performance benefits for repeated reads (caching)\n- Listers provide namespace-scoped caching with consistent indexers\n- Router's expected usage pattern involves watching resources and caching for lookups\n- Fake informers needed for controller unit tests\n\n### 4. Use kubebuilder/operator-sdk\n\n**Approach**: Use kubebuilder to scaffold and generate clients.\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- AgentCube does not follow kubebuilder project layout\n- Would require significant restructuring of existing codebase\n- kubebuilder generates controllers + webhooks; only client needed here\n- Overhead of kubebuilder annotations for simple client generation\n\n### 5. Skip fake clients\n\n**Approach**: Generate only real clients, no fake implementations.\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- Unit tests require fake clients to avoid cluster dependencies\n- Standard Kubernetes client-go package includes fake clients by convention\n- E2E and integration tests depend on fake clients for isolated testing\n- Minimal overhead: fake generation is automatic with main client generation","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775877464311,"end":1775877464319}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775877464348,"sessionID":"ses_285759645ffe2slctD9Dn1azJE","part":{"id":"prt_d7a8ba101001MaDsW0u86okKTG","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7a8a9c8a001VCBGptRED3IIoH","sessionID":"ses_285759645ffe2slctD9Dn1azJE","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":25397,"input":3821,"output":3258,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":18318}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775877467566,"sessionID":"ses_285759645ffe2slctD9Dn1azJE","part":{"id":"prt_d7a8badab001GW0FSnZhfeFxh9","messageID":"msg_d7a8ba134001JamIwTWTVnrMwK","sessionID":"ses_285759645ffe2slctD9Dn1azJE","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775877469675,"sessionID":"ses_285759645ffe2slctD9Dn1azJE","part":{"id":"prt_d7a8bafcd0015crTjATPGwaLXe","messageID":"msg_d7a8ba134001JamIwTWTVnrMwK","sessionID":"ses_285759645ffe2slctD9Dn1azJE","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_5061e1476cd24d55ac8920dc","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-034: CI/CD GitHub Actions\n2: \n3: ## Summary\n4: \n5: Implement comprehensive GitHub Actions CI/CD infrastructure for the AgentCube project, consisting of 12 automated workflows covering build verification, linting, testing, code generation, end-to-end testing, release automation, and contributor workflow approvals.\n6: \n7: ## Purpose\n8: \n9: ### Background\n10: \n11: The AgentCube project requires robust CI/CD automation to ensure code quality, catch regressions early, and automate release processes. The project consists of multiple components:\n12: \n13: - **Go-based Workload Manager** (`workload-manager`)\n14: - **Go-based AgentD Controller** (`agentd`)\n15: - **Python SDK** (`sdk-python`)\n16: - **Kubernetes manifests and Helm charts**\n17: \n18: The current manual build and test processes need automation through GitHub Actions to support:\n19: 1. Pull request validation on multiple code paths\n20: 2. Multi-architecture Docker image building and publishing\n21: 3. End-to-end testing in Kind clusters\n22: 4. Release automation with semantic versioning\n23: 5. Code quality enforcement (linting, spelling, copyright headers)\n24: \n25: ### Goal\n26: \n27: Implement 12 GitHub Actions workflows in `.github/workflows/` that:\n28: \n29: - Run on pull requests to `main` and `release-*` branches\n30: - Use path filtering to avoid unnecessary runs\n31: - Build and push Docker images to GitHub Container Registry\n32: - Run Go and Python tests with coverage reporting\n33: - Perform code generation drift checks\n34: - Execute end-to-end tests on Kind clusters\n35: - Enforce spelling and copyright compliance\n36: - Automate plugin publishing and workflow approvals\n37: \n38: ### Value\n39: \n40: | Benefit | Description |\n41: |---------|-------------|\n42: | **Automation** | Eliminates manual build/test/release steps |\n43: | **Consistency** | Ensures all PRs pass identical checks |\n44: | **Speed** | Path filtering skips irrelevant workflows |\n45: | **Reliability** | E2E tests catch integration issues |\n46: | **Release Efficiency** | Automated image publishing on tags |\n47: | **Quality** | Lint, spelling, copyright enforcement |\n48: \n49: ---\n50: \n51: ## Scope\n52: \n53: ### In-Scope\n54: \n55: | Workflow | Path | Description |\n56: |----------|------|-------------|\n57: | Agentcube CI Workflow | `.github/workflows/main.yml` | Docker build on PR |\n58: | Lint | `.github/workflows/lint.yml` | Go lint with golangci-lint |\n59: | Codegen Check | `.github/workflows/codegen-check.yml` | Verify generated code up-to-date |\n60: | Test Coverage | `.github/workflows/test-coverage.yml` | Go test with coverage |\n61: | E2E Tests | `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` | End-to-end testing on Kind |\n62: | Python SDK Tests | `.github/workflows/python-sdk-tests.yml` | Python SDK unit tests |\n63: | Python Lint | `.github/workflows/python-lint.yml` | Ruff Python linting |\n64: | Codespell | `.github/workflows/codespell.yml` | Spelling check |\n65: | Copyright Check | `.github/workflows/copyright-check.yml` | Copyright header enforcement |\n66: | Build and Push Release Images | `.github/workflows/build-push-release.yml` | Multi-arch image publishing |\n67: | Dify Plugin Publish | `.github/workflows/dify-plugin-publish.yml` | Plugin release automation |\n68: | Approve Workflows | `.github/workflows/workflows-approve.yml` | First-time contributor approval |\n69: \n70: ### Out-of-Scope\n71: \n72: - Jenkins or other CI systems\n73: - Cloud-specific deployments (AWS, GCP)\n74: - Custom GitHub runners\n75: - Performance benchmarking CI\n76: - Security scanning (Dependabot covers dependencies)\n77: \n78: ---\n79: \n80: ## Impact Analysis\n81: \n82: ### Dependencies\n83: \n84: | Dependency | Purpose | Status |\n85: |------------|---------|--------|\n86: | `docker/setup-buildx-action` | Docker buildx setup | Required |\n87: | `docker/login-action` | GHCR login | Required for releases |\n88: | `actions/checkout` | Repository checkout | Required |\n89: | `actions/setup-go` | Go environment | Required |\n90: | `actions/setup-python` | Python environment | Required for Python workflows |\n91: | `helm/kind-action` | Kind cluster creation | Required for E2E |\n92: | `dorny/paths-filter` | Path-based filtering | Required |\n93: | `codecov/codecov-action` | Coverage upload | Optional |\n94: | `aws-actions/configure-aws-credentials` | AWS ECR (future) | Not in initial scope |\n95: | `docker/build-push-action` | Multi-platform builds | Required |\n96: \n97: ### Upstream\n98: \n99: - `ci-cd/spec.md` — Requirements document\n100: - `ci-cd/design.md` — Technical design specifications\n101: - `Makefile` — Build targets referenced by workflows\n102: \n103: ### Downstream Consumers\n104: \n105: 1. **Contributors** — All PRs trigger workflow runs\n106: 2. **Release managers** — Tag pushes trigger image publishing\n107: 3. **End users** — Benefit from tested releases\n108: 4. **External plugins** — Dify plugin publishing workflow\n109: \n110: ### Risks\n111: \n112: | Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n113: |------|----------|------------|\n114: | Workflow run timeouts | Medium | Path filtering reduces unnecessary runs; separate jobs |\n115: | Flaky E2E tests | Medium | Artifact collection on failure; retry logic |\n116: | Concurrent workflow limits | Low | Queue management; prioritize main branch |\n117: | Secret exposure | High | Use GitHub secrets; minimize secret usage |\n118: | Dependabot workflow changes | Low | Pin action versions; review updates |\n119: \n120: ---\n121: \n122: ## Alternatives Considered\n123: \n124: ### Option 1: Single monolithic workflow (Not Selected)\n125: \n126: **Pros**: Single trigger, simpler structure\n127: **Cons**: No parallel execution; path filtering not granular; harder to debug\n128: \n129: ### Option 2: CircleCI or Jenkins (Not Selected)\n130: \n131: **Pros**: Mature platforms\n132: **Cons**: Vendor lock-in; requires infrastructure; inconsistent with GitHub ecosystem\n133: \n134: ### Option 3: GitLab CI (Not Selected)\n135: \n136: **Pros**: Built-in Auto DevOps\n137: **Cons**: Project not on GitLab; additional platform to maintain\n138: \n139: ### Option 4: 12 separate workflow files (Selected)\n140: \n141: **Pros**: Fine-grained path filtering; parallel execution; clear separation of concerns; each workflow can be debugged independently\n142: **Cons**: More files to maintain; shared conventions require discipline\n143: \n144: ---\n145: \n146: ## Technical Design\n147: \n148: ### Workflow Summary\n149: \n150: | # | Filename | Trigger | Path Filter | Key Jobs |\n151: |---|----------|---------|-------------|----------|\n152: | 1 | `main.yml` | PR: main, release-* | (none) | build |\n153: | 2 | `lint.yml` | PR: main, release-* | `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `.golangci.yml` | golangci |\n154: | 3 | `codegen-check.yml` | PR: main, release-* | `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, `Makefile` | codegen-check |\n155: | 4 | `test-coverage.yml` | PR, merge_group, workflow_call | `**` minus md/svg/png/docs | coverage |\n156: | 5 | `e2e.yml` | PR: main, release-* | (none) | e2e-test |\n157: | 6 | `python-sdk-tests.yml` | PR, merge_group | `sdk-python/**` | python-sdk-tests |\n158: | 7 | `python-lint.yml` | PR: main, release-* | `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `pyproject.toml` | python_lint |\n159: | 8 | `codespell.yml` | PR: main, release-* | (none) | codespell |\n160: | 9 | `copyright-check.yml` | PR: main, release-* | copyright: all except md/svg/png/docs/.github | build |\n161: | 10 | `build-push-release.yml` | push: main, tags v*.*.* | (none) | build-and-push |\n162: | 11 | `dify-plugin-publish.yml` | push: tags dify-plugin/v* | (none) | publish |\n163: | 12 | `workflows-approve.yml` | PR: main, release-** | (logic-based) | approve |\n164: \n165: ### Trigger Details\n166: \n167: **Pull Request Triggers:**\n168: - `main` branch — primary development branch\n169: - `release-*` pattern — release branches\n170: \n171: **Push Triggers:**\n172: - `main` branch — for latest image builds\n173: - Semantic version tags: `v*.*.*`, `v*.*.*-*` (e.g., `v1.2.3`, `v1.2.3-beta`)\n174: - Dify plugin tags: `dify-plugin/v*`\n175: \n176: ### Path Filters\n177: \n178: Uses `dorny/paths-filter` for efficient workflow triggering:\n179: \n180: | Filter Name | Patterns |\n181: |-------------|----------|\n182: | lint | `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, `.github/workflows/lint.yml` |\n183: | codegen | `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, `Makefile` |\n184: | coverage | `**` (all) minus `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`, `docs/**` |\n185: | copyright | All except `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`, `docs/**`, `.github/**` |\n186: | python | `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml` |\n187: | sdk | `sdk-python/**` |\n188: \n189: ### Environment Variables\n190: \n191: | Workflow | Variable | Value |\n192: |----------|----------|-------|\n193: | E2E | `ARTIFACTS_PATH` | `${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs` |\n194: | Release | `TAG` | `github.ref_name` (tag) or `latest` |\n195: | Release | `IMAGE_REGISTRY` | `ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}` |\n196: \n197: ### Secrets Required\n198: \n199: | Secret | Purpose | Workflows |\n200: |--------|---------|------------|\n201: | `GITHUB_TOKEN` | GHCR login, workflow approval | build-push-release, workflows-approve |\n202: | `CODECOV_TOKEN` | Coverage upload (optional) | test-coverage |\n203: | `GH_TOKEN` | Cross-repo plugin PR | dify-plugin-publish |\n204: \n205: ### Key Make Targets\n206: \n207: | Target | Workflow | Purpose |\n208: |--------|----------|---------|\n209: | `docker-build` | main.yml | Build workload manager image |\n210: | `docker-build-router` | e2e.yml | Build router image |\n211: | `docker-build-picod` | e2e.yml | Build picod image |\n212: | `docker-buildx-push` | build-push-release.yml | Push workload manager |\n213: | `docker-buildx-push-router` | build-push-release.yml | Push router image |\n214: | `docker-buildx-push-picod` | build-push-release.yml | Push picod image |\n215: | `lint` | lint.yml | Run golangci-lint |\n216: | `gen-check` | codegen-check.yml | Verify code generation |\n217: | `gen-copyright` | copyright-check.yml | Generate copyright headers |\n218: | `e2e` | e2e.yml | Run E2E tests |\n219: | `e2e-clean` | e2e.yml | Cleanup Kind cluster |\n220: \n221: ### Go Version Matrix\n222: \n223: | Workflow | Go Version |\n224: |----------|-------------|\n225: | lint.yml | 1.24 |\n226: | codegen-check.yml | 1.24.4 |\n227: | test-coverage.yml | 1.24 |\n228: | e2e.yml | 1.23 |\n229: | build-push-release.yml | 1.24.4 |\n230: \n231: ### Python Version Matrix\n232: \n233: | Workflow | Python Version |\n234: |----------|----------------|\n235: | python-sdk-tests.yml | 3.12 |\n236: | python-lint.yml | 3.10 |\n237: | codespell.yml | (system) |\n238: \n239: ### E2E Test Infrastructure\n240: \n241: **Kind Cluster:**\n242: - Name: `agentcube-e2e`\n243: - Kind version: v0.30.0\n244: - Created by: `kind create cluster` in `run_e2e.sh`\n245: \n246: **CRD Installation:**\n247: - Downloads agent-sandbox v0.1.1 by default\n248: - Applies manifest.yaml and extensions.yaml\n249: \n250: **Images Pre-loaded:**\n251: - `workloadmanager:latest` (built locally)\n252: - `agentcube-router:latest` (built locally)\n253: - `picod:latest` (built locally)\n254: - `redis:7-alpine` (pulled)\n255: - `python:3.9-slim` (pulled)\n256: \n257: **Port Forwards:**\n258: - Workload Manager: 8080 → service/workloadmanager:8080\n259: - Router: 8081 → service/agentcube-router:8080\n260: \n261: ---\n262: \n263: ## Implementation Plan\n264: \n265: ### Phase 1: Core Build & Lint Workflows\n266: \n267: - [ ] Create `.github/workflows/main.yml` — Docker build verification\n268: - [ ] Create `.github/workflows/lint.yml` — Go lint with path filter\n269: - [ ] Create `.github/workflows/codegen-check.yml` — Code generation verification\n270: \n271: ### Phase 2: Testing Workflows\n272: \n273: - [ ] Create `.github/workflows/test-coverage.yml` — Go coverage tests\n274: - [ ] Create `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` — Kind-based E2E tests\n275: - [ ] Create `.github/workflows/python-sdk-tests.yml` — Python SDK tests\n276: - [ ] Create `.github/workflows/python-lint.yml` — Ruff Python lint\n277: \n278: ### Phase 3: Quality Enforcement Workflows\n279: \n280: - [ ] Create `.github/workflows/codespell.yml` — Spelling checks\n281: - [ ] Create `.github/workflows/copyright-check.yml` — Header enforcement\n282: \n283: ### Phase 4: Release & Automation Workflows\n284: \n285: - [ ] Create `.github/workflows/build-push-release.yml` — Image publishing\n286: - [ ] Create `.github/workflows/dify-plugin-publish.yml` — Plugin release\n287: - [ ] Create `.github/workflows/workflows-approve.yml` — Contributor approval\n288: \n289: ### Phase 5: Integration\n290: \n291: - [ ] Add workflow dispatch for manual runs\n292: - [ ] Configure required status checks\n293: - [ ] Verify path filtering works correctly\n294: \n295: ---\n296: \n297: ## Acceptance Criteria\n298: \n299: | ID | Scenario | Expected Result |\n300: |----|----------|-----------------|\n301: | CI-001 | PR to main with Go changes | lint.yml and test-coverage.yml run |\n302: | CI-002 | PR to main with Python changes | python-lint.yml and python-sdk-tests.yml run |\n303: | CI-003 | PR with no relevant changes | No workflows trigger (path filter) |\n304: | CI-004 | Push to main branch | main.yml builds Docker image |\n305: | CI-005 | Tag push v1.0.0 | build-push-release.yml publishes images with tag v1.0.0 |\n306: | CI-006 | E2E workflow failure | Logs collected in e2e-logs artifact |\n307: | CI-007 | Codegen drift detected | Workflow fails with exit code |\n308: | CI-008 | Missing copyright header | copyright-check.yml fails |\n309: | CI-009 | Typo in code | codespell.yml fails |\n310: | CI-010 | First-time contributor PR | workflows-approve.yml queues for approval |\n311: | CI-011 | Dify plugin tag push | dify-plugin-publish.yml creates PR |\n312: | CI-012 | Workflow call from external | test-coverage.yml runs with optional token |\n313: \n314: ---\n315: \n316: ## Timeline Estimate\n317: \n318: | Phase | Workflows | Effort |\n319: |-------|-----------|--------|\n320: | Phase 1: Core Build & Lint | main, lint, codegen-check | 4 hours |\n321: | Phase 2: Testing | test-coverage, e2e, python-sdk-tests, python-lint | 6 hours |\n322: | Phase 3: Quality Enforcement | codespell, copyright-check | 2 hours |\n323: | Phase 4: Release & Automation | build-push-release, dify-plugin-publish, workflows-approve | 4 hours |\n324: | Phase 5: Integration | Testing, documentation | 2 hours |\n325: | **Total** | **12 workflows** | **18 hours** |\n326: \n327: ---\n328: \n329: ## Relationship to Other ARs\n330: \n331: This AR (AR-034) provides the CI/CD infrastructure that supports all other AgentCube implementation ARs:\n332: \n333: - **AR-029** (SDK HTTP Client) — Verified by python-sdk-tests.yml\n334: - **Future ARs** — Will use these workflows for validation\n335: \n336: The CI/CD infrastructure is foundational—without it, other ARs cannot be properly validated before merging.\n\n(End of file - total 336 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-034: CI/CD GitHub Actions\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement comprehensive GitHub Actions CI/CD infrastructure for the AgentCube project, consisting of 12 automated workflows covering build verification, linting, testing, code generation, end-to-end testing, release automation, and contributor workflow approvals.\n\n## Purpose\n\n### Background\n\nThe AgentCube project requires robust CI/CD automation to ensure code quality, catch regressions early, and automate release processes. The project consists of multiple components:\n\n- **Go-based Workload Manager** (`workload-manager`)\n- **Go-based AgentD Controller** (`agentd`)\n- **Python SDK** (`sdk-python`)\n- **Kubernetes manifests and Helm charts**\n\nThe current manual build and test processes need automation through GitHub Actions to support:\n1. Pull request validation on multiple code paths\n2. Multi-architecture Docker image building and publishing","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775877469658,"end":1775877469673}}}}
